  "diagnostic_features": [
    "Two sets of aromatic protons: α-protons (H-2, H-5) at ~7.31 ppm and β-protons (H-3, H-4) at ~7.05 ppm",
    "Characteristic coupling pattern with J values of ~5.1 Hz (α-β coupling) and ~3.6 Hz (β-β coupling)",
    "13C NMR shows α-carbons at ~127 ppm and β-carbons at ~124 ppm",
    "Strong IR absorption at 850-750 cm⁻¹ for out-of-plane C-H bending is diagnostic",
    "Substituent effects are more pronounced at α-positions (2,5) than β-positions (3,4)",
    "Electron-donating substituents cause significant upfield shifts, especially at α-positions"
  ]
